				<h4 id="syntax">
					Syntax
				</h4>
				<p>
					The syntax for the <mono>init</mono> command is:
<div align="center">
<pre class="prettyprint inline lang-nift" style="margin-bottom:-10px">
nift config --global user.name (username)
nift config --global user.email (address)
nsm config --global user.name (username)
nsm config --global user.email (address)
</pre>
</div>
				</p>

				<h4 id="description">
					Description
				</h4>
				<p>
					The <mono>config</mono> command is for getting and setting the username and email address configured with Git, this is particularly useful if installing through a package manager or app store which sandboxes <mono>Nift</mono> and requires Nift be bundled with <mono>Git</mono>. The syntax is almost identical to the syntax used with <mono>Git</mono>.
				</p>
